# {name}

{description}

## Install

```bash
pip install -e .
```

Or, if this tool ships inside a dazzlecmd-pattern aggregator, it is dispatchable as `dz {name}` (or via FQCN: `dz {namespace}:{name}`).

## Usage

```bash
{name} [arguments]
```

## Development

Run the tests:

```bash
pytest tests/
```

## Files

- `.dazzlecmd.json` -- tool manifest (consumed by dazzlecmd-lib at discovery)
- `{name_underscore}.py` -- the tool's entry point (exposes a `main(argv=None)` function)
- `tests/` -- pytest test suite (added by `dz new tool --full`)
- `TODO.md`, `NOTES.md`, `ROADMAP.md` -- developer notes (added by `--simple`/`--full`)
